        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Lebanon: Israeli strikes Beirut in new 'lage-scale' attack Middle East Issued on: 12/03/2026 - 14:38 Modified: 12/03/2026 - 14:45 #Israel launched a new 'large-scale attack' against #Hezbollah targets late on March 11, following rocket fire from the militant group. It struck #Beirut's southern suburbs as well as the capital's city centre, for the second time in a day and the third time since the start of the #war. Iran's new Supreme Leader Mojtaba Khamenei has 'very good links with the IRGC' 12/03/2026 Middle East Mojtaba Khamenei as Iran's new Supreme Leader signals continuity to international community 12/03/2026 Middle East Middle East war: Oil tankers set ablaze in the Gulf in latest Iranian attacks 12/03/2026 Middle East US war on Iran: 'An American war in desperate search of a strategy', expert says 12/03/2026 Middle East Banking, finance and consultancy firms evacuate staff in Gulf States 11/03/2026 Middle East 'Two decades in the making': Expert details how Mossad built its spy network in Iran 11/03/2026 Middle East US war on Iran: Using military force to achieve political outcomes rarely produces lasting stability 11/03/2026 Middle East Israel launches new 'large-scale' wave of strikes on south Beirut 11/03/2026 Middle East Iran may tap into organised crime to carry out terror attacks, expert says 11/03/2026 Middle East"
